1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,600
Don't try my patience.

2
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:17,567
Because you don't know
what else I can do to you.

3
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:19,300
I'm such a lousy mother.

4
00:00:19,367 --> 00:00:22,067
I don't judge you
for what you did.

5
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:24,767
I know you have a reason
for doing that.

6
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:29,133
Mommy Emma said I have
inner strength and resolve.

7
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:31,033
So, I need to be brave.

8
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,300
I need to be strong.

9
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:35,567
You can now walk
on your own, dear.

10
00:00:35,667 --> 00:00:39,067
All I need is to try
and believe.

11
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:39,733
Bruise.

12
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,300
Why do you have a bruise?

13
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:42,700
Flor, Mookie's missing!

14
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:44,300
Mookie's in her room.

15
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:45,367
- How did that...
- Are you stupid?

16
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:46,433
She's not there!

17
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:47,767
You can tell the police.

18
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:50,367
But it feels like
I'm betraying my mom.

19
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:51,567
Come here, you little brat!

20
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,500
Where did you go?

21
00:00:52,567 --> 00:00:54,333
And you stay away
from my daughter!

22
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,100
I'll call the cops!

23
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,267
I've already talked to Mon.

24
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:34,700
He knows a PAO lawyer.

25
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:37,167
They can help us for free.

26
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:42,100
Dan, I'm sure her mom
is hurting her.

27
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,533
Let's report it
to the authorities.

28
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:47,367
Are you still thinking about
Mookie and her mother, Emma?

29
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:50,433
You still haven't gotten out.
You're still in prison.

30
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:53,033
You should've seen
Mookie earlier.

31
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,467
She's not talking
because she's scared.

32
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,367
But she needs help.

33
00:01:57,267 --> 00:01:59,800
Emma, help yourself first.

34
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:03,133
Let's focus first
on how you can get out.

35
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:11,300
Where did you go?

36
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,967
Just there.

37
00:02:17,467 --> 00:02:19,033
Look at me...

38
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,067
when I'm talking to you.

39
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,633
Specifically...

40
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,967
where did you go?

41
00:02:34,067 --> 00:02:35,733
To the park.

42
00:02:38,167 --> 00:02:40,233
You're a terrible liar!

43
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:47,033
I called the police station.

44
00:02:48,867 --> 00:02:53,600
And they told me
you went there.

45
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,500
Dan, please believe me.

46
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:02,467
I'm very sure that her
mother is hurting her.

47
00:03:02,533 --> 00:03:04,700
We don't have proof.

48
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:07,267
Even if we report it to
the police,

49
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,367
it will only look like we want
to get even with her mom

50
00:03:09,433 --> 00:03:11,233
for sending you to jail.

51
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,000
Come on.

52
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,133
What if we report
it somewhere else?

53
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,733
Let's report it to
the barangay office.

54
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,200
If Olive finds out
we reported it,

55
00:03:18,267 --> 00:03:20,300
her anger towards the child
will only get worse.

56
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,100
Come on. You're not thinking.

57
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,133
How stupid are you...

58
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,600
to risk your life
and your health...

59
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,433
for a thief?

60
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:40,000
Answer me, Mookie.

61
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,700
Who do you love more?

62
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:49,567
Is it Emma or me?

63
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:59,600
Why aren't you answering?

64
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:05,133
You, Mommy.

65
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,300
You.

66
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:07,667
You're lying!

67
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:13,467
You're choosing Emma over me!

68
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:19,633
Because if you really love me,
you wouldn't go to her!

69
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:22,200
You wouldn't side with her!

70
00:04:29,467 --> 00:04:31,300
Mommy, I'm sorry.

71
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:33,067
Mommy.

72
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:38,700
You don't know how worried
I am for you, Mookie.

73
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:44,667
Everything that I do
for you, all of it,

74
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:46,733
means nothing to you.

75
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,700
Mommy, that's not true.

76
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:51,533
And do you know how
that makes me feel?

77
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:56,367
It makes me feel useless!

78
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:57,400
No, Mommy.

79
00:04:57,467 --> 00:04:59,033
That I'm a failure!

80
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:01,300
That I'm worthless!

81
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,267
Mommy, no.

82
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:06,133
No, Mommy.
It's not true, Mommy.

83
00:05:08,233 --> 00:05:11,433
I only want to stop her
from hurting Mookie.

84
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:16,367
Olive will make her life hell
as long as she's in that house.

85
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:17,600
Please have mercy on the child.

86
00:05:17,667 --> 00:05:19,933
Someone needs to save her.

87
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:23,433
You don't want me to go to
a radio station

88
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,300
because you don't want
to drag Mookie into it.

89
00:05:25,367 --> 00:05:27,367
And now you want me to report it
to the barangay office?

90
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:29,100
What are you thinking, Emma?

91
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:30,667
This is different, Dan.

92
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:34,267
This is not about letting people
know what Olive did to me.

93
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:36,733
The child is no longer
safe in that house.

94
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,033
What if her mother
hurts her again?

95
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:42,000
My guilt can't take it.

96
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:42,667
Dan!

97
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,033
I'm a terrible mother!

98
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:51,667
Mommy, no!

99
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:53,067
No, Mommy!

100
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,267
That's why you're
doing this to me!

101
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,500
Because I'm a bad person!

102
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:57,400
I'm bad!

103
00:05:57,467 --> 00:05:58,467
- Mommy, no!
- I'm bad!

104
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:00,067
Stop it!

105
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:01,567
Mommy, stop it!

106
00:06:01,633 --> 00:06:05,600
You do this to me because
I mean nothing to you.

107
00:06:05,667 --> 00:06:07,167
Mommy, I'm sorry.

108
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,700
I'm sorry, Mommy.
Please stop that.

109
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,100
Mommy.

110
00:06:11,167 --> 00:06:12,467
Mommy, no!

111
00:06:12,533 --> 00:06:16,200
No, no, no, no, Mommy!

112
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:17,233
Please!

113
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:17,933
No, Mommy!

114
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,267
You know, I better end my life

115
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:23,000
- so you can be with Emma!
- Mommy, no!

116
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,367
No, Mommy.

117
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,367
No!

118
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:26,667
No, Mommy!

119
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:27,367
No!

120
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:29,067
Mommy, no!

121
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:30,467
No!

122
00:06:30,533 --> 00:06:32,333
I'm sorry, Mommy!

123
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,500
I'm sorry!

124
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:35,367
Mommy, please!

125
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,367
Where did I fail?

126
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:40,267
Where did I go wrong, Mookie?

127
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:43,567
Where did I go wrong?

128
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:45,533
Where did I fail?

129
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,200
Mommy, please,
don't hurt yourself.

130
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:49,600
I'm sorry.

131
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:51,433
I'm sorry, Mommy.

132
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,067
Sorry.

133
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:58,033
Mommy, please.

134
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,933
I'm sorry.

135
00:07:05,033 --> 00:07:06,233
Mookie!

136
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,933
I'm sorry.

137
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,333
Mommy, I'm sorry.

138
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:22,033
Do you remember our bedtime
routine when you were a child?

139
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,000
Before you go to bed?

140
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,567
Yes, Mommy.

141
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:33,533
You were afraid of the dark.

142
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:40,933
You wanted the lights on,
even if you were going to sleep.

143
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,533
And then, I would do
this to you.

144
00:07:48,633 --> 00:07:50,500
And then I would tell you...

145
00:07:52,167 --> 00:07:54,567
to embrace the darkness.

146
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,067
And then,

147
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,900
think of something nice,

148
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:03,367
something good.

149
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:07,067
Something that will
become sweet dreams.

150
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,633
What are you thinking now,
sweetie?

151
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:31,567
Happy thoughts, Mommy.

152
00:08:34,267 --> 00:08:36,633
I'm thinking of
happy thoughts.

153
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:34,700
Emma.

154
00:09:39,033 --> 00:09:40,133
I'm glad you're awake.

155
00:09:40,667 --> 00:09:41,400
Here.

156
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:45,133
I brought you breakfast.

157
00:09:47,067 --> 00:09:49,533
It's from Kutsy and Wiro.

158
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,567
They're sending their regards.

159
00:09:55,167 --> 00:09:56,233
Spoon and fork.

160
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,000
Here's more. There's bread here.

161
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:03,500
Put it there.

162
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:06,567
Use it for your trash.

163
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:10,433
Mom, please thank them for me.

164
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,500
Where's your husband?

165
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:14,633
I didn't see him.

166
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:19,400
Hey.

167
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,600
You fought, didn't you?

168
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:28,700
Did you?

169
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:33,567
We just had an argument
about Mookie.

170
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,800
I knew it.

171
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:40,200
He's against reporting Mookie's
mother to the barangay office.

172
00:10:41,467 --> 00:10:43,333
Your husband is right.

173
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:46,733
It's not that easy.

174
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:49,667
You can't just do that.

175
00:10:50,767 --> 00:10:53,300
Even if you tell the truth,

176
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:55,733
that witch can easily
turn it against you.

177
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,233
She's a snob.

178
00:10:57,933 --> 00:11:00,367
The barangay staff only
need to talk to Mookie.

179
00:11:00,433 --> 00:11:03,133
I'm sure, she'll tell the truth.

180
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,933
You really are something.

181
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:10,000
You want another trouble.

182
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:13,067
Leave Mookie to her mother.

183
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:14,333
She's not your child.

184
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:22,000
I feel like I'm a mother
whenever I look after Mookie,

185
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:24,033
even though she's
not my flesh and blood.

186
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,300
That's why I won't neglect her.

187
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:30,467
You probably understand me
because you're a mother, too.

188
00:11:33,467 --> 00:11:36,100
I just don't want you
to get hurt even more.

189
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:39,033
Emma...

190
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:44,000
no matter how deeply you
love Mookie,

191
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:47,600
you're still not her mother.

192
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:50,667
That's just it.

193
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:54,600
Mom, I treat
Mookie as family.

194
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:56,400
So I won't give up on her.

195
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:57,700
I'll help her.

196
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:07,333
Come on, Mookie, you have
to finish your food.

197
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,167
You need to regain
your strength.

198
00:12:09,233 --> 00:12:12,533
Mommy, I really am not
in the mood.

199
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,633
What do you mean you're
not in the mood?

200
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:16,300
You've barely eaten.

201
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:19,000
And you're already full?

202
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:22,567
I don't really
have the appetite.

203
00:12:23,233 --> 00:12:24,667
Oh, Mookie.

204
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:27,000
I woke up early

205
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:29,567
so that I could prepare
this breakfast for you.

206
00:12:30,067 --> 00:12:32,667
Because I know that's
all your favorite.

207
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:34,733
Unless...

208
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,700
you already have a new favorite.

209
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:44,767
I really don't feel well, Mommy.

210
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:46,067
Oh, dear.

211
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:50,500
See what happens when
you disobey the rules?

212
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:55,300
You probably inhaled all
the virus at the police station.

213
00:12:55,367 --> 00:12:57,767
And now, you're sick again.

214
00:13:04,133 --> 00:13:05,167
Okay, Mookie.

215
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,533
It's time for your meds.

216
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:10,400
Why?

217
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:12,633
- Wait.
- Mommy, I think

218
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:14,400
- I'm throwing up.
- I'll get the vomit bag.

219
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:19,200
Here.

220
00:13:19,267 --> 00:13:20,233
Are you going to throw up?

221
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,233
- Yes.
- Here.

222
00:13:30,467 --> 00:13:34,000
Are you really throwing up,
or are you making excuses?

223
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:43,333
Stop. This is it.

224
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,167
This is it.

225
00:13:50,567 --> 00:13:51,567
Really, Dan?

226
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:53,200
You reported her
to the barangay?

227
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:54,267
Yes, Emma.

228
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:56,700
You know I can't ignore you.

229
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,700
Besides, if Mookie's
mother is hurting her,

230
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:03,600
I'll feel guilty if I don't
do anything to help her.

231
00:14:03,667 --> 00:14:04,967
Thank you.

232
00:14:05,033 --> 00:14:08,300
I feel relieved.

233
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:11,567
I also thought
about our daughter.

234
00:14:11,633 --> 00:14:16,067
If she was alive, I wouldn't
let anyone abuse her.

235
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:19,067
No one has the right
to hurt a child.

236
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:22,267
You shouldn't do that even
if you're the parent.

237
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:22,967
Correct.

238
00:14:24,367 --> 00:14:26,267
Are you really throwing up?

239
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:29,133
Or you just don't want
to take this medicine?

240
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:34,200
You know, I don't understand
you.

241
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:40,167
You need to take your medicines
if you want to get better.

242
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:44,000
Mommy, please, no.

243
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,067
- Mommy.
- Come on.

244
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:47,633
Mommy, please, no.

245
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:48,400
Mommy, please!

246
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:49,433
- Let go!
- I don't want that!

247
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,033
That hurts, Mommy!

248
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:54,067
- You need this!
- Mommy, I don't want that!

249
00:14:57,833 --> 00:14:59,033
Look what you did!

250
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,700
Good afternoon, Dra. Caparas.

251
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:35,500
Chairwoman Reyes

252
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,700
and Councilor Torres
of Barangay Sunnyside.

253
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:39,567
May we talk to you?

254
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:43,567
What can I help you with?

255
00:15:44,467 --> 00:15:45,600
Is this about a donation?

256
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:47,667
Just leave the
solicitation letter.

257
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:48,367
No.

258
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:50,700
That's not what we're here for.

259
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:54,000
May we go inside?

260
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,033
How rude of me.

261
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,333
I don't have a helper.

262
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,333
The house isn't tidy.

263
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,233
That's why I don't
accept visitors.

264
00:16:02,933 --> 00:16:06,233
Then let me tell you the
reason for our visit.

265
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:09,600
We received a complaint
against you.

266
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:14,533
And as per protocol,
we came here to hear your side.

267
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:17,400
Complaint?

268
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:20,967
About what?

269
00:16:22,367 --> 00:16:24,567
About possible child abuse.

270
00:16:27,067 --> 00:16:27,567
What?

271
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,367
I think you're mistaken.

272
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,633
There is no child
abuse going on here.

273
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:36,233
I'm sorry, Doc.

274
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:39,233
But the protocol is that
when there is a complaint,

275
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:42,100
we have to go
and check it out.

276
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:48,000
If I may ask,
who filed the complaint?

277
00:16:48,067 --> 00:16:50,267
We can't tell you.

278
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,567
Doctor, we need to
talk to your child.

279
00:16:55,133 --> 00:16:58,067
My child has
a medical condition.

280
00:16:58,133 --> 00:17:00,033
Many people don't understand

281
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:05,133
the things I need to do
to ensure my child is safe.

282
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:08,500
And some people think
I'm locking her up.

283
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:12,367
Is this really necessary?

284
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:15,567
My daughter is not
in the best of health.

285
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,567
It's necessary.

286
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:19,667
May we go inside?

287
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:35,067
Aren't you scared?

288
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:37,633
We're going against an
influential person.

289
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:39,400
I'm thinking about that, too.

290
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:42,967
But it's time for people
to know the harm

291
00:17:43,033 --> 00:17:45,100
that Ma'am Olive is doing.

292
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:49,733
Please come in.

293
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:52,600
Mookie.

294
00:17:55,667 --> 00:17:57,267
They want to talk to you.

295
00:18:02,733 --> 00:18:04,200
Come here, sweetie.

296
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:05,267
Let me help you.

297
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:14,600
Can you manage?

298
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:24,167
Slowly.

299
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:27,333
Mookie, sweetie,

300
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:31,100
this is Barangay Captain Reyes
and Councilor Torres.

301
00:18:31,167 --> 00:18:32,500
Good day.

302
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:33,733
Good day.

303
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:36,500
Doctor, we need to
talk to her alone.

304
00:18:36,567 --> 00:18:37,633
It's a protocol.

305
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,300
Of course.

306
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:52,667
Will you be okay on
your own, Mookie?

307
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,000
Yes, Mommy.

308
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,367
Be careful with your answers.

309
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,433
Slowly.

310
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:17,300
Dan, is there
already an update?

311
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:19,333
They're still there.

312
00:19:20,667 --> 00:19:21,533
But...

313
00:19:23,367 --> 00:19:25,933
do you think we're
doing the right thing?

314
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:26,967
Why?

315
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:30,233
I just thought about it, Emma.

316
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,167
What happens if Mookie
tells the truth

317
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:34,500
and is taken by the DSWD?

318
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:36,633
What will happen to her?

319
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:40,500
Do you think it'll be
helpful for her?

320
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:44,600
She should be in good hands

321
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:47,200
rather than continuously being
harmed by her mother.

322
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:50,200
I'll leave you
for now, sweetie.

323
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,300
Solo, Ma'am.

324
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:05,233
Of course.

325
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,700
I'll be right here
if you need me.

326
00:20:23,733 --> 00:20:27,200
May I know how you
got your bruise?

327
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:37,567
This?

328
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:55,167
May I know how you
got your bruise?

329
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:06,500
I easily get bruises.

330
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:11,333
Dear, we want
to make you understand

331
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:15,133
that no one will know
everything we'll talk about.

332
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,700
Everything will
remain confidential.

333
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,300
Even to mommy?

334
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,633
To everyone.

335
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,700
Even to your mommy.

336
00:21:27,133 --> 00:21:28,267
Especially to her.

337
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:36,000
Are you sure?

338
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:37,733
Rest assured, dear.

339
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:49,267
Is there something
going on at home

340
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:50,600
that you don't think is right?

341
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:04,667
Do you think she'll talk?

342
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:07,400
Will she confess?

343
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:13,167
Is anyone hurting you, Mookie?

344
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:31,367
I think she'll have the
courage to speak up.

345
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,700
She'll tell the truth.

346
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:37,267
Is there anything you
want to tell us, dear?

347
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:48,300
We're here to protect you.

348
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:53,733
Where will you take me,
just in case?

349
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,700
We'll bring you with us.

350
00:22:56,767 --> 00:22:58,067
We'll take you away from here.

351
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,400
What about mommy?

352
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:13,233
What will you do to her?

353
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:16,333
Everything will go through
the proper process.

354
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:19,133
But your welfare
is our priority.

355
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:22,567
She can't get near you.

356
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,667
Do you want to go with us, dear?

357
00:23:59,367 --> 00:24:02,200
You're fighting for her,
but who did she side with?

358
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:02,667
Did she side with you?
I'm scared, Mom.

359
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:06,600
I don't know what her
mother can do to her.

360
00:24:06,667 --> 00:24:08,333
Where will you take my daughter?

361
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,433
I can explain.

362
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:11,500
Whatever she told you...

363
00:24:11,567 --> 00:24:14,000
I told them the truth, Mommy.

364
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:15,533
What?

365
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:18,567
Pursuing the case against Emma

366
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:20,967
is a lose-lose situation
for you.

367
00:24:21,033 --> 00:24:23,133
I have to make sure
that she doesn't squeal.

368
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:27,567
I'll make sure that she
can't tell the authorities.
